n\n== Exhibitions ==\nCatania presented one of his sculptures created with silicone and acrylic at the Radisson Hotel's rooftop gala dinner and in Grimaldi Forum in Montecarlo during the Rolex Master Cup 2018.<ref name=\"italiachiamaitalia.it\">{{cite web|url=http://www.italiachiamaitalia.it/artisti-italiani-allestero-a-cannes-selezionato-cesare-catania/|title=Artisti italiani all\u2019estero, a Cannes selezionato Cesare Catania - Italia chiama Italia|date=10 May 2018|publisher=}}</ref>\n\nIn the 2017 his artworks made with waste and scrap were exhibited in the \u201cLa Fabbrica del Vapore\u201d Contemporary Art Museum of Milan.<ref name=\"auto\">{{cite web|url=http://www.arte.it/calendario-arte/cosenza/mostra-cesare-catania-reart-37509|title=Cesare Catania. ReArt - Mostra - Cosenza - Sedi varie - Arte.it|first=ARTE.it Srl -|last=info@arte.it|website=www.arte.it}}</ref> \nIn the 2016 art exhibitions were held in Louvre (Paris), Vatican and in Lugano (CH) during an international event supported by the President of the Italian Republic , by the Foreign Ministry and by Italian Embassy.<ref name=\"tio.ch\">{{cite web|url=https://www.tio.ch/agenda/mostre-e-incontri/1110687/l-artista-cesare-catania-espone-a-lugano|title=L\u2019artista Cesare Catania espone a Lugano|date=12 October 2016|publisher=}}</ref> \nHis artwork \"The Embrace \u2013 B Version\", a tapestry, oil on canvas, was entirely done with a spatula. The embrace is understood by the author in the strict sense between a man and a woman, in an enlarged sense between people of two different colors. The themes of anti-Semitism and racism are reconciled for Cesare Catania in a hug.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://luxurylifeinternational.com/beauty-and-fashion/page/3/|title=Beauty & Fashion - Luxury Life International Magazine|publisher=}}</ref>\nHe also participated in 7th Biennale of International Art in Montecarlo in 2016.<ref name=\"paeseitaliapress.it\">{{cite web|url=http://www.paeseitaliapress.it/news_3786_Alla-Biennale-di-Montecarlo-anche-l-artista-italiano-Cesare-Catania.html|title=Alla Biennale di Montecarlo anche l'artista italiano Cesare Catania|publisher=}}</ref> His work ''\"L'abbraccio''\", a tapestry, oil on canvas, entirely made with a spatula was presented at the occasion of the \"Italian Language Week in the world\" held in [[Lugano]], at the [[Helvetic Institute]]. The event was sponsored by the [[Consulate General of Italy (Henry P. Davison House)|Consulate General of Italy]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.agendalugano.ch/events/37315/cesare-catania-l-abbraccio|title=Cesare Catania - L'abbraccio|website=agendalugano.ch|access-date=2018-07-31}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.tio.ch/agenda/mostre-e-incontri/1110687/l-artista-cesare-catania-espone-a-lugano|title=L\u2019artista Cesare Catania espone a Lugano|date=2016-10-12|work=Ticinonline|access-date=2018-07-31|language=it-IT}}</ref>\n\n==Literary career==\nIn 2017, Catania published his first art book called ''Genesis: the Idea of Contemporary Art for Cesare Catania'' ({{ISBN|8822872401}}) <ref name=\"italiachiamaitalia.it\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://books.google.com.bd/books?isbn=8822872401|title=isbn:8822872401 - Google Search|website=books.google.com.bd}}</ref>\n\n==Works==\nOther notable works of art includes:\n* \"Metaphysical Composition\" (2016),\n* \"Artistic Composition\" (2016),\n* \"The Dynamics of the Movement\" (2016) \n* \"Vanity\" (2014), \n* \"Flamingos in the Mirror\" (2015)\n* \"144 : Jazz Trio\" (2014)\n* \"Nice (tribute to Matisse and Chagall)\" (2015) \n* \"Summer Readings (tribute to Pierluigi Nervi)\" (2016).\n* \"The Tear\" (2012)\n* \u201cThe Embrace \u2013 B Version\u201d (2016) - <ref name=\"tio.ch\"/>\n* \u201cThe Mouth of Etna \u2013 E Version\u201d (2018) \u2013 the first artwork studied for colourblind people - <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.monacolifestylemagazine.com/2017/11/22/great-success-cesare-catania-last-exhibition-monaco/|title=Great success of Cesare Catania during the last exhibition in Monaco - Monaco Lifestyle Magazine|date=22 November 2017|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://monacowealthmanagement.com/news/2017/09/29/art-everyone-advantage-colourblind/|title=Art for Everyone: the Advantage of being Colourblind - Monaco Wealth Management|first=Monaco Wealth|last=Management|date=29 September 2017|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cultart.it/cesare-catania-mostra-montecarlo-informazioni-video/|title=Cesare Catania e la nuova opera \"La Bocca dell\u2019Etna\"|date=5 October 2017|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.nbc-2.com/story/38189688/cesare-catania-exhibits-his-art-in-cannes-during-the-cannes-film-festival-period |title=Archived copy |access-date=2018-08-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180806024448/http://www.nbc-2.com/story/38189688/cesare-catania-exhibits-his-art-in-cannes-during-the-cannes-film-festival-period |archive-date=2018-08-06 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n* \u201cReArt\u201d ( 2017) <ref name=\"auto\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.laprovinciacr.it/arte/arte/170465/il-moderno-leonardo-da-vinci-cesare-catania-espone-reart-2017.html|title=\u201cIl moderno Leonardo da Vinci\u201d, Cesare Catania espone ReArt (2017|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.controluce.it/notizie/cesare-catania-larte-dei-rifiuti-urbani/|title=Cesare Catania e l\u2019arte dei rifiuti urbani|date=17 March 2017|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.arte.it/calendario-arte/milano/mostra-cesare-catania-reart-40513|title=Cesare Catania. ReArt - Mostra - Milano - Fabbrica del Vapore - Arte.it|first=ARTE.it Srl -|last=info@arte.it|website=www.arte.it}}</ref>\n* \u201cGospel\u201d (2016) \u2013 biennal art exposition of Monaco Montecarlo - <ref name=\"paeseitaliapress.it\"/>\n* \u201cThe Man who does not see\u201d (2013) \n* \u201cAleftina and her dolls\u201d (2016) \n* \u201cThe Woman on the Sofa\u201d (2016) \n* \u201cSelfportrait\u201d (2016) \n* \u201cTrois Hommes\u